2016 WW51 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver Release Announcement (BKC #4)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2016 WW51 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n Linux/\n \n VMWare/\n \n Windows\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

Test Result:

\xc2\xb7       Finish Silver test execution on\nRHEL 7.2 and Windows2016. Please visit HPQC for test details. Refer to the installation guide for\nthe BKC package installation

\xc2\xb7      Bakerville(RP Board: Yuba\nCity RP\nfab3)

o   Total test cases: 18; Passed test cases is 12 and pass\nrate is 66.67%. 

o   Test coverage:  

\xc2\xa7     SKX-D  ES1 SoC: Run P1  test cases on RHEL 7.2 and Windows2016.

\n   HW Rework \n
\n
\n
\n
\n
\n
\n \n \n \n \n
\n
HW rework:
  • No HW rework need for Yuba City fab3 board.
  • jumper setting refers to this link.
Work around:

  • When you flash onboard Aspeed BMC, in order to detect onboard dTPM in AC cycle, you need run below IPMI command in UEFI Shell:
            #cmdtool  20 C0 3f 07
